						<summary>

						<p>Base (Probably plinth) of the Kāśī Viśvēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>IMMAḌI CHIKKARĀYA</p>						

						<p>1817 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Śaka year 1738, Dhātu, Māgha, ba. 5, corresponding to Febraury 6, Thursday 1817 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that the construction of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> and a stone gateway and also donation of the <hi rend="italic">utsavavigraha</hi> of the goddess Chaṇḍīśvara by Immaḍi Chikkarāyalu, for the merit of his father Immaḍi Chikkarāyalu of Suguṭūri family.</p>						

						</summary>
